\,a,b,m\in\Bbb Z\;
\;\Bbb Z/m\Bbb Z\;\;:\;(a+m\Bbb Z)(b+m\Bbb Z)=ab+m\Bbb Z\;
\Bbb Z/m\Bbb Z\;\;\text{is a field}\;\iff \;\forall\,a\notin m\Bbb Z\;\exists\, b\in\Bbb Z\;\;s.t.\;\;ab+m\Bbb Z=1+m\Bbb Z\;\iff
\iff\;\forall\;a\in\Bbb Z\;\;s.t.\;m\nmid a\;\;\exists\,b,x\in\Bbb Z\;\;\text{with}\;\;ab+mx=1\iff \;g.c.d(a,m)=1\,\iff
